 A `Json.Decode.Decoder` for `PairDict`s, encoded by `encodePair`.

The order of insertion is not reconstructed (see `equal`)

    """
    [
     {
      \"left\": 2,
      \"right\": 22
     },
     {
      \"left\": 1,
      \"right\": 11
     }
    ]
    """
    |>Decode.decodeString
        (PairDict.decode
          Decode.int Decode.int
        )

> `Ok (Pairs [ ( 1, 11 ), ( 2, 22 ) ])` = a `PairDict`
